definition.value: A C-nitro compound that is propanoic acid in which one of the methyl hydrogens has been replaced by a nitro group.
A is a monophosphoglyceric acid having the phosphate group at the 3-position as well as an alpha-D-mannosyl residue attached at the 2-position.
A 1-pyrrolinecarboxylic acid having a hydroxy substituent at the 4-position.
